AGI - Rai has sent a letter of disciplinary dispute to Serena Bortone regarding the post published by the journalist on its social profiles on April 20 regarding the story Scurati. As with practice in the contest, journalists are asked for any justification and clarification." It makes known the company of Viale Mazzini. Concept reiterated shortly after the ad Rai, Roberto Sergio, in audition in commission of Vigilance: "It is not a disciplinary measure but a request for clarification and explanation. And then you can decide what actions to take. It's a dispute, not a measure." The same manager then told his about the case of the writer whose intervention to the program "What will be", with a monologue on Liberation, was cancelled: "On the Scurati affair - Sergio said - it was not forbidden neither the participation of the guest nor the reading of the monologue. Never was the participation or reading of the monologue, which was then represented by Mrs. Bortone in transmission. These are the facts." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"It was challenged to Serena Bortone, as happened in similar cases, the post published on social in violation of corporate policy legislation: There are rules that must be respected by all employees. The law prohibits making public statements about business, news or business. The contest is a due act and will follow the procedure provided for in the regulation," said Ad Rai, Roberto Sergio.
&nbsp;
The managing director himself recalled that "it is &nbsp; in closing an audit of which we will have the final results shortly, we can anticipate that the aspects examined will be two: the first possible procedural disalignments in the operating process, and I can say that surely there have been; the second, behaviours of individuals with regard to which reports on the incident were promptly requested. The overall outcome of these double checks will be assessed improving processes and/or interventions towards employees." For the Rai's ad, this story "has created a reputational damage to the company and all employees, with an accusation of non-existent censorship." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
On the case Bortone also intervened the dg of Rai, Giampaolo Rossi:&nbsp; "If there is an equality of rights - he said - there is also an equality of duties. He's trying to see if there were any violations." On the necessary authorization to make statements, Rossi stressed that "it's for the general manager as well as for the last of the employees." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
For the Usigrai, the proceedings initiated against Serena Bortone are unacceptable. "And so he did: Roberto Sergio, the man who, as head of Rai, director of the radio, publicly attacked the Giornale Radio Rai on social media, now as managing director fustiga to blows of disciplinary proceedings who, also through social defends his freedom, and professionalism' from a system of control "asphyxiating" on the work of journalists of the Rai", comments on social Daniele Macheda, secretary Usigrai, who adds: "The measures announced on the Scurati affair have therefore arrived but to the wrong person. The disciplinary procedure open to Serena Bortone is unacceptable. That's enough." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
For the deputy of Alleanza Verdi Sinistra, Angelo Bonelli, intervened in commission of Vigilance where the audition of the ad Roberto Sergio and dg Giampaolo Rossi is taking place, "it is a very dark situation from the point of view of the democracy of our country - he added - I invite you to reflect, is an extremely serious fact". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Deputy Bortone aside,&nbsp; Rai's ad, Roberto&nbsp;Sergio, spoke in audition in commission of Vigilance of so much more. First of all, the company of Viale Mazzini, who, in his opinion, "is the victim of a destructive anger". "An anger - it has explained - that it seeks to counteract facts, data, numbers, concrete results and verifiable of the imaginative reconstructions when not of the infamous accusations that not only harm the reputation and value of the Rai but that mortify the community of women and men that every day works to bring in the houses of the Italians the best of their abilities".
&nbsp;
"The Rai - said Sergio - not only does not deserve this treatment but needs to be protected and defended by fakenews built to art to discredit and get some title in the newspapers". &nbsp;Sergio&nbsp; also stressed that "a year of mandate has recorded positive results also on the front of the audience's appreciation. Also in this case unfortunately we had to attend a series of mystifications and instrumentalizations that have had as the sole objective to discredit a valuable asset like the Rai".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
For Sergio, "the generalist Rai networks both in the entire year 2023 and in this first quadrimestre of 2024 confirm the leadership of the listens. This is true both throughout the day and in the first time - it has added - despite the impacts of the further reduction of the limits of advertising crowding previewed for 2023, the advertising collection has recorded an increase of more ' 22 million euros, to further demonstration of the appeal of Rai products. Once again we must forget and overturn the 'news' that wants to listen and consequent advertising revenues in decrease". Sergio also said he had "chiesto&nbsp; to the director Stefano Coletta to insert 'Insider' in the next summer or winter palimpsests", about the program of Roberto Saviano not aired.
&nbsp;
Sergio also faced the chapter of Franco Di Mare, the war envoy struck by an incurable tumor that a few weeks ago had 'demnified' the latitude of the company of viale Mazzini which he had addressed to ask for the state of service with the list of the places he had worked. :&nbsp; "It was sent yesterday, through pec, the documentation he had requested," he assured the ad.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Another topic touched in the Supervisory Committee, the comparison between all political leaders in view of the European elections: "We're working to make sure that we can accommodate the confrontation between the leaders: there will be a single confrontation between all the candidates before the vote, we work so that it can be hosted" on the Rai.
&nbsp;
Finally, going back a few months, again the Sanremo Festival with the polemics related to the 'sponsored' exhibition on the stage of the John Travolta's Arizona: "From the inside audit - said Sergio - it has emerged that neither the employees nor the external collaborators of the Rai were aware of the will of the actor to wear the shoes with the logo of the company U-Power, not recognized before the entrance. The contract concluded with the company Divina Luna expressly provided for the prohibition of introducing elements of advertising or promotional value if not authorized by Rai. The performance has violated the agreements, we have initiated an action to the civil court of Rome, under the charge of Divina Luna and U-Power, for non-compliance and violation of the obligations of fairness, for damages also considered. Moreover, the payment of the entire compensation for Travolta's performance has been suspended." "If the company that represents Travolta has intended to make agreements that go beyond the indications envisaged, it is not known, we are not involved, we would be if the facts happened were ascertained" concluded the Rai ad.
&nbsp;

