AGI -&nbsp;"The Constitution is of all because it touches everyone" and for this reason "I think it is a mistake to approach these issues with an ideological approach, but it is the prevailing orientation I see so far in this debate" on the premiership. With this premise, the President of the Council, Giorgia&nbsp; Meloni, began his speech at the conference "The Constitution of All. Dialogue on the premiership", organized at the Chamber. By expressing satisfaction in seeing a audience composed not only of professionals, but above all by personalities of the world of entertainment, sport and entrepreneurship, &nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; he then stressed that it serves political stability to the Country> and that the premier goes in this direction "leaving unchanged the fundamental powers of the President of the Republic", but, at the same time, "eliminating to the political function of the Republic incapable".
&nbsp;
"It is necessary to safeguard the guarantee bodies, starting with the function of arbitrator super partes of the head of the state and exactly what this reform does," he clarified &nbsp; Meloni. Among the objectives of the prime minister, he continued, there is to ensure that "who is chosen by the people to govern can do so with a legislative horizon, can have time to carry out the program with which he presented himself to the citizens: time and stability are a decisive factor in building any strategy and thus to restore credibility to our institutions in the face of citizens and this nation with our international interlocutors." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Meloni&nbsp; he also hoped that the premier will be approved by Parliament >" with a majority of two-thirds, but if this does not happen the word will pass to the Italians, as it provides for our constitution." The premier then observed: "It's a customization error. >This reform does not concern the subscriber or the president &nbsp;Mattarella. It's about another world, a hypothetical future. For this it is worth discussing instead of always customizing everything. I had no problem voting for the cut of Members. There are issues on which the opposition ends itself is useless. This tactical game pays the citizens and credibility of the institutions." In addition, "I am convinced that we would do good service to the nation if we accompanied" the premier to "an electoral law that reconstructs the electoral-elector relationship and consolidates the democracy of alternation" reintroducing preferences.
&nbsp;
"I believe I was the president of the only party who had the courage to table amendments that reintroduced the preferences for the election of MPs, I have never been contrary and also on this I am open," he added. "Today the international context does not allow us lightness, lightness can be really dramatic," continued &nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; reiterated several times the need to have political stability, governments. "This - he has finally observed - is a solid, stable government, > I do not need to do this reform, for me it is a risk" >, but the more we can stand on the merit and the more we can get to a text, I do not know how much shared, but better, as long as we talk about the merits of the matter". The conference was attended by some famous faces of the showbiz: from Iva Zanicchi to the TV host Pupo, by actress Claudia Gerini to singer-songwriter Amedeo Minghi. And then the former Italian swimming champion Filippo Magnini, Tunisian entrepreneur and film producer Tarak Ben Ammar and manager Pietro Salini.&nbsp;

