AGI - "You have avoided further aggravation of the situation. I join the call of Secretary General Guterres to avoid military operations in Rafah for the dramatic consequences that might have on Palestinian civilians." The President of the Republic Sergio Mattarella > said this by speaking to the General Assembly of the UN.
<h2>"Continuing support for Unrwa"</h2>
"It is necessary to consider the essential function of the United Nations Agency for the Rescue and Employment of Palestinian Refugees in the Near East and consequently the importance of continuing to finance it," said Mattarella, "to end the chain of actions and reactions and allow the start of a process that ends the massacres, finally lead to a stable peace: a solution that necessarily passes by the shared objective of full and mutual recognition of the two States of Israel and Palestine, with the definitive recognition of Israel and its security by the States of the region". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"The ceasefire, requested by the Security Council with Resolution 2728, unconditional humanitarian access to the people of Gaza, the release of hostages seized during the inhuman attack of October 7 - which, underlined, is the cause of what happened subsequently - and the immediate interruption of all the activities of support to terrorist organizations, remain the charges on which to continue to build with determination. The harshest and hardest conflict cannot allow to violate the norms of humanitarian law, enshrined in the Geneva Conventions of 1949, to protect civilian populations," said the President of the Republic.
<h2> The attack on Ukraine is even more serious for the role of Moscow
"The aggression made by the Russian Federation to Ukraine contradicts the founding reasons of the UN and is even more serious as coming from one of the countries on which greater responsibility falls in the international community, as a permanent member of the Security Council," continued the head of the State, "spinte vetero-nazionalistiche, neo-imperialist impulses if not neo-colonialiste, competition between powers in place It is more important than ever, then, to strengthen multilateral institutions, beginning with the United Nations."
&nbsp;
"Peace is interest of all peoples, everywhere. Italy, with other international partners, is committed to seeking a peaceful and lasting solution to the conflict. Not any solution >o, at least, a solution that rewards the aggressor and mortifies the attack", he emphasized, "creating a precedent of great danger for all. It is not a question of creating a purchesia composition. Peace, to be fair, must be based on the high and irrelevant principles of international law and the Charter of the United Nations".
